added.title: Something to Remember
added.description: On the last day of Yong Bao's visit to Sodor, his friends dig up a giant keepsake to help him remember them.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Sandy Versus the Storm
added.description: When a big storm approaches, Thomas and company must complete all a week's worth of deliveries by the end-of-the-workday whistle, but when Sandy needs repairs, Thomas and the gang will realize just how important Sandy is to the team!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Nature Explorer
added.description: Bing and his friends are Nature Explorers today! But what will happen when Bing is nature exploring by a big, prickly bush?

added.title: Choosing
added.description: Bing and Flop are at Padget's shop today choosing a toy to buy. And it's tricky hard to pick just one! And what will happen when Bing thinks he has made the wrong choice and wants to swap?

added.title: Dark
added.description: It's time for bed, but where's Hoppity? Bing thinks he's left him outside, and now, it's all dark... With the help of Flop and his carroty torch, can Bing find Hoppity in time for bed?

added.title: Stuck
added.description: Bing & Sula are climbing on trees in the Howly Woods today, and it's tricky-hard! Sula needs Bing's help to climb up, and get back down again. But what will happen when Bing wants to climb up even higher?

added.title: Cake
added.description: Bing is having a cake party today, and is excited to show Sula the raspberry he decorated the cake with especially for her. But it's hard for Sula to see, so what happens when Bing tilts the cake a little too far?

added.title: Dirty Dog
added.description: Pato is enjoying watering his flowers when all of a sudden he notices that something smells horrible. It's Loula: she stinks. Elly is putting on perfume, and she too notices how bad Loula smells. Pooey! When Pocoyo can't eat his sandwich because Loula smells so bad, he makes a plan. Loula needs a wash. The only problem is, Loula doesn't want to get in the bath and gives chase to Pocoyo, Elly and Pato. Pocoyo and his friends decide to trick Loula into a cleaning machine but their plan is thwarted. However will they stop the smell? Then, all of a sudden it begins to rain and Loula finally gets her long-awaited clean.

added.title: Invisible Pocoyo
added.description: Pocoyo finds a fantastic new toy: a machine that makes things invisible! He wants to show his friends his exciting discovery but they are too busy doing their own thing. Pocoyo is miffed but then realizes that he can have some fun with them, without them knowing about it. He makes himself invisible and starts to undertake various sneaky antics which utterly dumbfound his pals. Things get out of hand when Pato blames Elly and Elly blames Pato - even though we all know it's really Pocoyo's fault. Finally the truth is revealed when Baby Bird presses the button on the machine and Pocoyo is de-invisible-ised! In the end, they all play at being invisible together.

added.title: Runaway Hat
added.description: It's a windy day and Pato's hat gets blown away. Pato doesn't like the way he looks without his hat and he's afraid his friends will laugh at him so he hides and won't play. Finally they catch up with him and he tries on a selection of replacement hats, none of which quite fit the bill. When Elly and Pocoyo realize what's wrong they don't understand Pato's reaction. They like the way he looks. Pato comes to see that his friends love him for who he is, not what he looks like and the friends all play happily together.

added.title: Noise to My Ears
added.description: Pocoyo, Elly and Baby Bird have great fun making lots of noise. But what's music to their ears is a real old racket to poor Pato who's trying to have a nap. Pocoyo, Elly and Baby Bird agree to try to be more considerate. But then they find another wonderful way to make music - by bouncing balls. Again, their music wakes up the sleepy duck. Finally Pocoyo and his chums make a cacophony with lots of machines. Pato completely loses his cool. Pocoyo's attempt at a soothing lullaby does nothing to calm the ever-more exhausted quacker. Pato realizes there's no other way round this - he's going to have to conduct them himself. In so doing, he really gets into it and the music gives him lots of energy. He's no longer sleepy and everyone's playing brilliant harmonious music together.

added.title: The Seed
added.description: Pocoyo finds a seed. He can't wait for it to grow. He guards it lovingly but can't prevent his friends from taking an interest in the seed too. Sleepy Bird thinks it would make a tasty snack but Pocoyo stops her from munching it just in time. Loula thinks it's a toy to bury and Pato thinks it's an egg. Finally Pocoyo erects a comprehensive security system to protect his seed but Elly accidentally knocks it over. Pocoyo's seed grows into a beautiful flower. But Loula picks it and shakes it. Pocoyo is upset until he realizes - -with our help - that Loula's shaking of the flower has simply made more seeds fall on the ground, and therefore more beautiful flowers have grown.

added.title: Yes Yes Vegetables Song - Healthy Habits!
added.description: Baby Izzy doesn't like vegetables - until they sing a song with her!

added.title: Sandcastle
added.description: Blippi and TABBS go to the beach, where they meet Crabby the Crab! A local expert on sandcastles, Crabby teaches them how to build a castle that can't get washed away!

added.title: No Monsters Scared of the Dark
added.description: The Baby Pumpkins are scared of the dark as they go to the halloween party!

added.title: Yip Yip, Book Book!/Stick to It!
added.description: It's the Pretty Big All City Read and Izzy and Barb are ready, that is, until all the books go missing!/Pretty Big City finds itself in a sticky situation when the factory starts spewing super sticky slime everywhere!

added.title: The Treasure of Treetop Woods/Zee Makes an Amazing Maze!
added.description: Ranger Nat's hike turns to adventure when he finds a treasure map. The only problem is that he can't read it./Zee and MacBarm are setting up their corn maze with the help of Zee's Zee Mobile… that is, until it breaks down inside the maze.

added.title: Boot Castle/Avocado's Long Time Out/Tanks Giving
added.description: Findley discovers a boot that him and Lucas use as a castle./ When they hear Avocado has been put in her naughty crate, Lucas and Findley entertain her./ Lucas brings Dimples things from around the house so she doesn't feel left out.

added.title: Flying/Dr. Lucas is in the House/Arlo's Portrait
added.description: After watching Findley in flight, Lucas wonders what it would be like to fly./ Dr. Lucas tries to make all his friends feel better but ends up under the weather himself./ Lucas decides to paint a portrait of Arlo. But Arlo can't sit still.

added.title: A Day With Starmush
added.description: Mush-Mush wants to be just like Starmush when he grows up, because he's convinced that Starmush is the most awesome Mushable there is and that his daily life must be extraordinary. So, Mush-Mush trails Starmush, which soon annoys the Mushelder. To get rid of Mush-Mush, Starmush decides to live up to the Mushler's fantasies…

added.title: Dare For More
added.description: Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit are playing dares and having a lot fun. All the Mushables are happy for them except Fung and Miff who keep mocking them. When Mush-Mush reply they should play together to see how fun it is, Fung and Miff accept. Mush-Mush surprisingly gets along with Fung and Miff until one dare too many.

added.title: Plunk to the Rescue
added.description: When Plunk discovers that Cheer and the Bears are working with Robbie to foil Bluster's latest bad scheme, he's eager to help out, even if Robbie objects and Cheer thinks it's best that he sits this mission out.

added.title: Once Upon a Rainbow
added.description: When Grumpy mysteriously loses his blue color in a far-off area of the Silver Lining, the Bears track down the cause: a creature called the Painter has lost the key to the magical paintbox that creates all the color in the area. Grumpy must recover the key to restore his blueness.

added.title: After the Klatternack
added.description: The Care Bears try to capture the Klatternack, a comical creature whose non-stop nonsense is annoying the local Whiffles. The Bears are joined by the ultra-serious Tracker, who has long been after the Klatternack himself. But despite their combined efforts, the wily creature continues to elude them - until Share realizes there is more going on than meets the eye.

added.title: Let the Fun Shine
added.description: Expert skateboarder Funshine tries to duplicate the in-the-groove fun Dibble has when she rides her little cloud like a skateboard, but he discovers along the way that having fun isn't always about a better skateboard or riding a cloud, it can be about trying harder at something and finally succeeding.

added.title: Sorry Not Sorry
added.description: While observing an ancient Whiffle ritual, Grumpy accidentally steps on a sentient plant. When his apology sends the plant and Whiffles into an upset, Share helps him learn how to genuinely apologize from his heart, and that a real apology is about how the other person feels, not about yourself.

added.title: Let Them Make Cake
added.description: Melissa wants cake, but she wants the other babies to bake it for her.

added.title: Mind Your Manners
added.description: The babies learn proper dinner etiquette when preparing to dine out with Granny.

added.title: Petunia the Piggy Bank
added.description: The kids start getting an allowance but only Petunia thinks to save for something special.

added.title: A Pastime for Petunia
added.description: Petunia has a difficult time finding a hobby that doesn't imitate the other babies' interests.

added.title: Pouting Match
added.description: Lola tries pouting to get what she wants, and soon all the babies are doing it.

added.title: Blippi Learns Rainbow Colors
added.description: Have you ever wondered how a rainbow gets its colors? Join Blippi and his sidekick TABBS on their first adventure as they discover the science behind rainbows!

added.title: Wheels on the Bus
added.description: Ella and Mummy take the big red bus to Lellobee farm, where she meets Mia and the rest of the team!

removed.title: The Incredible Shrinking Bears
removed.description: Frustrated that she's too small to reach even the bottom-most berries on a tree, Dibble becomes the tallest member of the team when a strange cloud of magical fog shrinks the Care Bears to miniature size. To save them, she must race against time to get them to a reversal-fog that will return them to their normal size.

removed.title: Do You Speak Dance/A New Spider in Town/Dollhouse Mates
removed.description: "Maizie" keeps ignoring Lucas and Findley, but not only do they learn she has a cousin, they also learn a new skill!/ Lucas befriends a bright purple toy spider, and Findley gets jealous./ Lucas and Findley move into the dollhouse together.

removed.title: Letting Off Steam
removed.description: When Thomas and Percy get into their first big fight they're afraid that their friendship is over... until Nia helps them figure out how to resolve it.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Ice Cream
removed.description: It's hot out and Bing and Flop are trying to catch up to Gilly to get some ice cream! Bing finally catches up with Gilly and gets his yummy delicious carroty ice cream. Does he drop his ice cream as he waves goodbye?

removed.title: Dandelion
removed.description: Bing finds a dandelion in the park and loves blowing the seeds and watching them fly away! He decides to save the last one to give it to Sula, but will he be able to keep the seeds from blowing away in the wind as he takes it to her?

removed.title: Baby Bird Bother
removed.description: Baby Bird is in awe of Pocoyo as he plays skillfully with a bouncy ball. Baby Bird continues to admire Pocoyo but this time it's his construction skills as Pocoyo plays with his blocks. And yes, Baby Bird thinks Pocoyo is the best at painting too. At first Pocoyo thinks it's great to have an admirer but soon, Pocoyo can't do anything without Baby Bird interrupting. Eventually Pocoyo gets so frustrated that he sends Baby Bird away. Pocoyo enjoys doing everything all by himself but it's not long before he wonders where his friend Baby Bird has gone. When Pocoyo realizes that Baby Bird was only trying to be his friend Pocoyo decides to invite Baby Bird to a party especially for him.

removed.title: Loose Change
removed.description: Sylvester is upset when Granny paints the bedroom but he learns the importance of change.

removed.title: Yours, Mine...and Mine, Mine!
removed.description: Daffy thinks if he shares his old toys, Granny will buy him all new toys.

removed.title: Act Your Age
removed.description: The kids try to see who can act most like a baby, while vying for Granny's attention.

removed.title: Puff's Perfect Picnic
removed.description: Because he has won the moss-ball game last year, Puff is in charge of organizing this Summer's Picnic. Only Puff isn't comfortable in that role. Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit offer to help and make sure all the Mushables will follow Puff's lead. Gradually, Puff gains confidence and ends up bossing everyone around. Now, all the Mushables are about to flee the Picnic!

removed.title: Finders Keepers
removed.description: When Dibble loses her beloved playball, the Care Bears are shocked to discover it has been taken by the Keeper, a mysterious figure who collects and stores away all items lost in the Silver Lining. To regain possession of the ball, the Bears and Dibble must help the Keeper recover a loss of his own.

removed.title: Picture Perfect Park Party/Sun Block
removed.description: Hero Celebration Day is finishing with a slideshow of everyday heroes, that is, until the projector screen rips./Pretty Big City is cooling off with an ice slide in the park, but the situation gets slippery when the slide starts melting.

removed.title: Bandages
removed.description: Bing and Coco are nurses today after Coco gets a paper cut on her finger and needs a bandage. But Bing would like a bandage too, and makes one from sticky tape. But what will happen when he tries to take it off and it hurts?

removed.title: My Pato
removed.description: Pato and Elly are arguing over their blocks when Caterpillar and Baby Bird walk past with presents for Pato. Oh no! Pocoyo and Elly have forgotten Pato's birthday. Elly is quick to whisk Pato off to a birthday picnic, determined to prove how much she cares. Not to be outdone, quick-thinking Pocoyo appears at the picnic with a present but Elly retaliates and 'accidentally' breaks it. Pocoyo and Elly fight so hard over Pato that he's almost broken in two. Fed up with all the fight Pato packs his things and is about to leave. When Pocoyo and Elly realize that their fighting has driven Pato away, they quickly make up and turn their efforts into making a special birthday party for Pato.

removed.title: Wash Your Hands, Scrub That Soap
removed.description: Ella is getting muddy. Mei comes out with a plate of dumplings, but Ella's hands are dirty!

removed.title: Boo!
removed.description: Pocoyo has a new game which he enjoys playing on his friends: BOO! Only some of his friends find Pocoyo's game annoying or frightening. But this only encourages Pocoyo more. He boos poor Pato til he ends up a nervous wreck. Elly sees how scared Pato has become and decides to give Pocoyo a taste of his own medicine. Elly makes Pocoyo jump. At first Pocoyo doesn't like it but ultimately Pato and Pocoyo both realize it can be fun to BOO! and to be BOOED!

removed.title: Roll Chickens, Roll!/Ramp Up, Up, And Away
removed.description: Farmer MacBarm is hosting the Sunny Field Farm Chicken Roll, but the race gets off to a slow start when the chickens don't roll./Ranger Nat can't wait to see Pinecone's Comet, that is, until his telescope falls to the bottom of a cliff.

removed.title: Party Pooper
removed.description: Pocoyo is having a party and invites all his friends. But instead of letting his friends have fun, Pocoyo keeps bossing them around. Pato, Elly and Fred soon get fed up and leave the party to play their own way. Left to play on his own, Pocoyo realizes that a party with no guests is no fun at all. Pocoyo invites his friends back to the party and everyone has fun playing together in their own unique and individual ways.

removed.title: Nia's Perfect Plan
removed.description: Nia has volunteered for a big day of deliveries and is determined to make the perfect plan to get it done, but when things start to go awry, she doggedly sticks to her plan and refuses any help.

removed.title: Lost in Space
removed.description: Pocoyo goes to visit his alien friend who wants to show him around his beautiful planet. Pocoyo and the alien have so much fun with the new things that they see and hear that soon they don't know where they are. At first they both panic but Pocoyo realizes with the narrator's and viewers' help that if he tries to remember the last place he was he'll be sure to find his way home.

removed.title: Star Helpers
removed.description: Starmush's back is stuck, and the Mushelder has no choice but to ask for help in Mushton. Because Chep is the one that finds a solution to his back problem, Starmush chooses him to help with his daily activities. But Mush-Mush is jealous, he would have loved being the chosen one…

removed.title: Wise Quacker
removed.description: Melissa gets laughs doing hurtful impressions of the other kids, but she takes the jokes too far.

removed.title: Who's Your Granny?
removed.description: When Granny gets sick, Lola tries to take over her responsibilities.

removed.title: Voosh
removed.description: Bing is vooshing with Hoppity around the garden, and Hoppity is vooshing higher and higher. But what happens when Hoppity vooshes so high that he disappears?

removed.title: Cat
removed.description: Bing loves playing with Arlo the cat, but what happens when Bing meets a new cat, who isn't so friendly?

removed.title: Lucas We Have a Problem/Egg-Scuse Me/Pokey Dokey
removed.description: Lucas helps Bodhi fulfill her dream of touching a star./ Lucas finds an egg and decides to take care of it. But he learns that responsibility is hard./ When Avocado loses her beloved toy, Lucas and Findley are determined to cheer her up.

removed.title: Gravity
removed.description: Three, two, one, lift-off! On this mission to the moon, Blippi bounces around with Rocky the Moon Rock. Light as a feather they bound up and float back down, teaching Blippi all about gravity! One small step for Blippi, one giant leap for Blippi.
